{
  "stem": "19923.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And after the war, of course, Fannie, my oldest sister, wanted to become a nun.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She already started taking her vows.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And she was she became a die hard Catholic convert.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And what happened is that after the war, my cousins had difficulty getting them-- getting them out of the convent even for visitation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So one weekend, they spirited my sisters out of there and while they took them out, they shipped them to London to my cousin-- to my uncles, Herman [?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Gottesdien ?] and Charles Gordon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And while in London, it took them six weeks to deprogram her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He said when he started talking to her, she would spit fire and brimstone at him.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Christ is going to punish you and all the Catholic dogma.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she really wanted to become a Catholic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But after six weeks, she finally realized that she's better off going back to her roots.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So then when she came back, they wouldn't give her back to the Catholic-- to the Catholic convent.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the Catholic convent started a lawsuit against my cousin, saying that they had a prior claim to my sisters.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they said the only one that could claim her was my mother, who was not around.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They said that my cousins didn't have a prior claim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But before the issue could be resolved, my sisters were able to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The American Jewish organization part of the-- I forgot the exact name, but it was part of a Jewish program to bring and reunite families of displaced people who had survived the war.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my two sisters came here in 1948.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "19-- they survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
